    "name": "Kampaeng Ngam Hotel",
    "detail": "A little quiet hotel at one of the little roads but near enough to walk to the 7-11 and night market. Staff were really friendly and helpful - we asked for extra pillows and were told that guests have to pay extra for the pillows. I think because our stay was almost a week long, one of the staff let us have two complimentary pillows eventually. Helps a lot for someone that had an ATV accident in Chiang Mai and needed to sleep comfortably to recuperate. Did not buy hotel breakfast when buying room nights but right outside the hotel, along the streets are little local stalls and restaurants so need not worry about food. Rooms and bathrooms are quite big, good for families travelling with young children. Pool is small but very clean.",
